  "texts": [
    "While the I5.0 paradigm is still making its debut in the industrial sector, there is an urgent need for more research presenting its practical implementation within factories focusing on ecosystem sustainability and worker well-being.",
    "• Lack of practical prototypes for small to medium enterprises (SMEs): Most Industry 5.0 research focuses on conceptual frameworks or large-scale industrial implementations with very little emphasis on small to mediumsized factories.",
    "Various researchers [36,51] attribute the scarcity or languidness in implementing state-of-the-art technologies, GenAI applications such as chatbots in this case, to the shortage of tailored innovative and practical solutions for small to medium-sized manufacturing enterprises and lack of initial capital to devote to advanced technologies.",
    "This field requires more research on the practical integration of GenAI applications such as chatbots to improve operational manufacturing processes and boost its adoption within the sector.",
    "Addressing identified gapsThis research addresses these gaps by the following:• Developing a GPT-based industrial bot inspired by a small manufacturing environment: Unlike existing chatbot applications, we design our GPT-based specifically for manufacturing environments, integrating production monitoring, fault diagnosis, and synthetic data generation capabilities."
  ],
